CN738_6FmYgTauJZAhshHw.text: Quality of ingredients is average to below average.  The interior is below average (cramped upstairs and just plain dingy downstairs).  But....the welcome is excellent and the variety on the menu is impressive).  Prices are low so it inevitably has become a haunt for us local workers at lunchtime.  Portions are so big its easy to feel ill afterwards so beware (especially the 4 egg omelette).  Not a great place, but not bad and certainly better than the local competition.

CW7nuZxdWXZPRZ1y9e5GyA.text: Dropped in for lunch last week and loved the place. Great food, very friendly and helpful service, excellent value. They also have much more on the menu than all-day breakfasts, pies, chips etc - I had the falafel and it was delicious. Plenty of vegetarian dishes and yummy home-made desserts too. The place is deceptively spacious, with seating on three levels. So if you walk in and the main shop looks crowded, do explore below. It's well worth it!

ejef4VBmNW932eeHWIN3cQ.text: A truly local British Cafe where you can enjoy a British fry up breakfast all day, and they have different levels of fry ups depending on how hungry you are. The set breakfast or the full breakfast should be able to satisfy most people's needs. However if you do have a big appetite or you have a incredible craving for the fry up, you can go for the Kennington special or the ultimate the builder's breakfast. They do have other items on the menu including pies and sandwiches but no matter what you ordered you can almost guarantee that you will walk away feeling very satisfied.

lTZfFxDFtTlSl7XJIpWWSQ.text: You really can't beat the full English breakfast here. I got porridge, full English and coffee. Probably enough for 2 people but you won't want to share it. All for under 10£

i88NBMvjdx9HLdAkJpYL3w.text: Brought my daughter here before a local appointment. It was her first time at a caff and we couldn't have chosen a better place. It's really like stepping into the glorious past. Friendly, fast, tasty and cheap! Perfect.

iEmQJJuxamHiJsLxlqLkUA.text: Waking up in our first morning in London, the only thing we wanted was a proper English breakfast. A short walk away from where we were staying was the Kennington Lane Cafe. We weren't sure if this was the place we wanted to commit to at first (you know how that goes!), but we were so happy that we did! Very friendly and welcoming staff, paired with fast service, made this place more than memorable. Large portions tied with wallet-friendly prices gave us the energy we needed to take on the city for the rest of the day. Next time we're in London we will have to grab the Full Breakfast here once, at least!

Of4f5qj2qXSvrhbu7LyQcg.text: Really friendly staff, great hearty food, just what we were after for a traditional English breakfast!

REakGKRAl9ADc8NRQVnSgg.text: Great local cafe! Got breakfast here twice when I stayed in London for a week with friends! They give you a lot of food for a great price and everyone is so nice!

XaQ6R_m04mUe0iBpWfwX7g.text: An absolute HOLE IN THE WALL for all you breakfast lovers! This was the first stop my girlfriend and I made immediately after we arrived in London. After reading a bunch of Yelp and Tripadvisor reviews, in addition to be starved after our train ride from Leicester we were craving for some breakfast and it only seemed right to stop by here! We were seated and immediately greeted by the owner (boy was he chatty and helpful), I ordered the all english breakfast set and my girlfriend decided on the spanish omelette. It exceeded our expectations and you won't be disappointed if you come in hungry (it kept us full for a good 5 hours). We'll definitely be coming back in the future the next time we vacation London!

ceCATWlQPMxs7todrnRNUA.text: Excellent service, very friendly and welcoming. Food was very good and filling (got the full breakfast).

3qkEc_K4AIjzHiL1-Tp0WQ.text: One of my favorite breakfast spots to go to when I was staying in London! They had huge portions for a good price. The staff was very helpful and friendly. It was usually packed when I went there but the atmosphere was very good old fashion cafe. You can tell that lot of people there were regulars.

VV00N8posckly5XA0GqDcg.text: HIGHLY recommended!! The owner Halil was very friendly and welcoming. He greeted every customer who came in, and the rest of the staff was nice, too. My husband and I wanted to eat a true English breakfast and at somewhere close to our hotel. We chose the right place! Halil took our order and gave us the option of half beans and half tin tomatoes for no extra charge, so that we could try everything. Because on the menu, it says served with the beans "or" tomatoes. Because I don't eat as much, I chose the Full Breakfast, and my husband chose the Kennington Special, which is the true full English breakfast. The portions were plentiful and at reasonable prices!Details of the food items.. The bacon is not like American style; it looks like ham, but it's not. It's more like a simple cured pork, but still very good. The sausage is similar to American breakfast sausage, but a little less spicy and thicker (bigger links). My husband says it's the best thing on the plate. It's definitely very good! I would describe the fried slice as like fried funnel cake batter as a toast. The beans are similar to American baked beans, but not as sweet and with no barbecue flavor- a surprisingly pleasant accompaniment. Tin tomatoes are basically warmed-up canned, stewed tomatoes. I don't usually like tomatoes, especially big chunks or pieces of them, but I liked these. They complemented the bacon very well. The regular slice is basically regular, buttered toast. Black pudding is blood sausage. The taste was a mild sausage-like flavor with no blood taste at all. It paired well (and was actually recommended by Halil) with the bubble, which was basically a veggie hash. The mushrooms were sautéed, sliced and diced mushrooms.The service was quick and everything tasted great! Kennington Lane Café is a brunch place, but also serves regular lunch. My husband and I checked out the rest of their menu and everything else on it sounded awesome too. They have a great variety of choices and we really thought about going back for late lunch. Their upstairs seating reminded us of American diner style and they have downstairs seating too. Whatever you all choose to go eat, you won't be disappointed!

tc7B1MjwCuNGwBlWLVAi9A.text: Traditional full english breakfast.  The sausages were good, the bacon was like slices of ham, the eggs were cooked just right and the toast underneath was toasted/buttered just right.  Lastly, I opted for the tin tomatoes rather than the black pudding.The milk tea was a little off for me, but it could just be I'm not used to it.  Maybe too much milk for me?

ETGfe-ZzsqVFfCG-PhSDOg.text: I typically don't write reviews but I had to for this place.  I'm backpacking across Europe and decided to stop in London.  I was looking for a true English breakfast and this place did not disappoint.  Halil sat down right next to me to explain the menu as I told him it was my first time to try any of this.  The service was amazing and the food matched the service! A must go-to if you're looking for a traditional meal

yzMRXa3DFAckPejzRvd0wg.text: This is a must if you're staying in the Lambeth area in London and being just a few minutes walk from Vauxhill Station it's definitely worth it. He was charming, engaging and funny and more importantly made sure your food order was proper and to your liking. And speaking of the food, it was equally incredible. And although it was a small cafe it had several options to choose from, from a traditional English to a vegetarian one. I personally had the Builder's Breakfast and I didn't leave with any space left. With lunch and dinner options as well, you can't miss at any time of day. So, for a low key, well done food experience away from the hustle of busy downtown London, you needn't look any further than here.

9EGTVfNW7R2mg3GEy7cuVw.text: We had a 930 am appointment at the us embassy so stopped here for breakfast. i9_Pq20yG3bTzYq4AHhbiA.text: Probably one of my favorite meals while I was in London. We came for a "last breakfast" before we left London. We still hadn't gotten a proper English breakfast. My friends were judging the cafe based on the outside and were a little apprehensive but I knew we had to go! To clarify, there's nothing wrong with the outside it's just small little unassuming cafe. We walked by the cafe every morning (it was near our place) and you can tell the locals frequent this cafe, so you know it's good! They have different breakfast combinations. My friends were more conservative than me and got the "Full Breakfast" I was being extra so I got the "Builders Breakfast" which is pretty much their biggest breakfast. Our meals came with a coffee (which honestly tasted like a latte-- not complaining) which is a nice touch. Everything was quick and delicious.Not only was the food delicious, service was wonderful as well. They make you feel at home and welcomed. One of the men who worked there even gave us an umbrella because he saw us standing under the awning while it was raining after our breakfast. He asked how we heard of the restaurant and I said Yelp, and he responded with "Of course, you Americans!!" Enjoyed my meal and experience here a lot!!

I tried a piece of black pudding (blood sausage) from my cousin's and it definitely tastes better than it sounds!! Should try it if you have not tried it! The owner, Halil, a sweet and funny man who made sure we all were enjoying our food. For my last day in London I wanted to try a full English breakfast and my overall experience was excellent.
